      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">501.670</ph> Category Managers.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d36e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d35e18" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                    Category
managers are responsible for identifying inefficient purchasing
behavior and crafting smarter buying strategies within specific
areas of spend as described in Government-wide Category Management,
Guidance Document issued by the Office of Management Budget, available
at <xref href="https://hallways.cap.gsa.gov/information/Gov-wide_CM_Guidance_V1.pdf"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">https://hallways.cap.gsa.gov/information/Gov-wide_CM_Guidance_V1.pdf</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d35e31" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                     <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Transactional
data.</i> Category managers should use transactional data collected
via clauses <xref href="GSAM-i1876737.dita#i1876737"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">552.216-75</xref> and <ph class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref href="GSAM-i1874125.dita#i1874125"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">552.238-80</xref> Alternate
I</ph> in conjunction with commercial market benchmarks to identify
potential areas for improvement in contracting methods, pricing,
and terms or conditions.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
